																		I Get It, You Hate Resurrection
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610249682" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;" >A Random Day</a></span> <span class="odate time_1448317655 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Nov 2015 22:27</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2412579">
									

<p>Sure, I wrote this <a href="http://i3.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/000/875/511/a69.png">too late for the main wave of Resurrection and too early for its renaissance</a>, but I thought we needed to see a tale that reflects the critics' opinions (in a heavily distorted way).</p>
<p>Many thanks to Decibelles, thedeadlymoose, and Dexanote for their feedback and encouragement. Many thanks to GreenWolf, MrWrong, and psul for critique.</p>
<p>See more of my work on my <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/dr-arvind-desais-personnel-file">author page</a>!</p>

							</div>

								
