<p>I am obligated to register my annoyance at this being posted a month or two early pre-hiatus-end (especially because it still reads like an intro tale and we have too many intro tales), but I still really like it. I find the character appealing, the writing both realistic and wry, and it's fun to read despite the structure/concept.</p>
